observations.recommendation:
a. The Municipal Accountant to:
i. submit all DVs and AAR LRs as enumerated in 2019 Annex 1 hereof;
ii. adopt appropriate measures to henceforth ensure the timely processing, review and recognition of cash advance liquidation;
iii. henceforth, comply with the required certification imposed by Paragraph 1.1 of COA Circular No. 2012-001 on all cash advances, attesting that previous cash advances have been liquidated and accounted for in the books, and refrain from further granting cash advances to officials/employees with outstanding advances prior to liquidation thereof in line with Section 89 of PD 1445, among others;
iv. intensify internal control over the review procedures applied in the received requests for cash advance, LRs and its supporting documents, to discourage incomplete submission thereof; and
v. cause the submission of the complete list of cash advances liquidation recognized in advance at the end of CY 2019 to determine and record the necessary adjusting journal entries, and henceforth, discontinue such practice of advance recognition in order to promote fairness in the financial statements.

b. The Municipal Mayor to:
i. henceforth, enforce strict compliance of the required supporting documents in availing of cash advances and liquidation thereof, by all officers and employees of the Municipal Government, particularly those who are usually availing of cash advances; and
ii. ensure that all applicable laws, rules and regulations in the granting and liquidation of cash advances, as well as in the recording thereof, are steadfastly observed to foster fairness in financial reporting and to safeguard the funds of the LGU.

That the Municipal Budget Officer:
a. strictly monitor the budgets of all line items under MOOE, among others, and avoid authorizing expenses in excess in absence of duly approved appropriation;
b. henceforth, ensure that all requests for budget augmentation and are reviewed and approved by the Sangguniang Bayan;
c. mitigate the deficiency in the budget of both the GF-Proper and Market Operation so as to enable it to pay its own loan amortization.; and
d. That the Mun. Planning and Dev’t Coordinator:
e. ensure that the sufficiency of appropriate funding sources for loan amortizations before endorsing plans of loan applications to finance LGU projectsf. That the Local Chief Executive ensure implementation of all identified PPAs in accordance with the approved appropriation/budget of the report.

That the Municipal Accountant:
a. provide necessary supporting details of the PDAF balances which remained outstanding in the books for years;
b. ensure immediate settlement of the PDAF balances by remitting it to the national treasury in light of the decision of Supreme Court;
c. to refund excess project fund, other than PDAF, to the respective source or otherwise request for transfer to its General Fund, whichever is applicable, in accordance with the agreement and terms of grants.
d. That the Local Chief Executive to direct the Heads of implementing departments (Municipal Agriculture Office, Municipal Engineering Office, MSWDO etc), in coordination with the Municipal Accountant, to implement promptly the corresponding PPAs funded by grants and liquidate timely the amount granted.

a. Refrain from incurring expenses in excess of the approved appropriation/budget line items in conformity with existing law;
b. Ensure implementation of all identified PPAs in accordance with the approved programs;
c. Avoid reallocation of unutilized budgets from one expense class to another without the appropriate authority/legal bases;
d. Stop transferring of appropriation from one line item to another within the same expense class unless savings/surplus are properly identified;
e. Ensure that the Budget Officer revisit and strictly observes Sections 344 and 475 (Qualifications, Powers and Duties of the Budget Officer) of the Local Government Code of 1991 to strengthen budgetary controls expected from the department.

a. Increase the budget appropriation for the LCPC to at least one percent (1%) of the IRA, in accordance with the Juvenile Justice and Welfare Act of 2006, starting the CY 2018 and annually thereafter;
b. Expand the scope of LCPC PPAs so as to be responsive to the needs relative to the promotion and protection of the physical, moral, spiritual, intellectual, social well-being and welfare in general of children;
c. Utilize LCPC budget in accordance with the approved appropriation.

